The paper deals with the problem of inferring the topology of a network using measurements available at the end nodes, which is a common problem in computer networks. The use of interference between paths in the network is a novel approach to solving this problem, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The formulation of the problem as an integer program and the development of polynomial time algorithms suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of simulations to evaluate the performance of the proposed method suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-categories.
